 :tx/rationale "SYNTHESIS: The build-lock problem is the tip of a massive iceberg. What we need is not just 'edit/verify separation' but the FIRST PRACTICAL IMPLEMENTATION of spec/19-topology.md's coordination framework. The build lock maps to the coupling matrix: agents sharing CARGO_TARGET_DIR have coupling=1.0 on the build artifact. The fix maps to Π (assignment policy): assign agents to NON-OVERLAPPING file sets + SEPARATE target dirs. The deeper fix maps to ADR-TOPOLOGY-004 (topology-as-compilation): we can DERIVE the optimal agent assignment from the task dependency graph, because tasks trace to spec elements which trace to implementation files. The compilation pipeline: Task graph → file coupling IR → agent partition → assignment with disjoint file sets + per-agent target dirs → parallel edit → sequential verify. This is Stage 3 functionality, but the COLD_START algorithm for n<=5 agents is achievable at Stage 1. The key insight: CALM stratification means EDITING is Tier M (monotonic, parallel) and VERIFICATION is Tier NM (non-monotonic, sequential barrier). We already proved this empirically: 3 agents editing different files in parallel works; they only conflict at build time."
